-- MOVES-BofA top trading executives leave as job cuts loom-Bloomberg
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Wed Sep 10, 2014 12:44PM EDT
-- None



Sept 10 (Reuters) - Bank of America Corp's <BAC.N> two top trading executives have departed as the bank gets ready to eliminate fixed-income and equities jobs worldwide, Bloomberg reported, citing people familiar with the matter.

David Moore, chief of North American rates trading, and David Hartney, global head of futures execution, left this week, Bloomberg reported. (http://bloom.bg/1AyU0gZ) Moore joined the bank in 2011 after more than two decades at Morgan Stanley <MS.N>, where he ran the United States and European interest-rates unit, the report said. Hartney joined in 2012 after almost 18 years at JPMorgan Chase & Co <JPM.N>, the report added.